    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 5.24,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.06,
      "end": 11.82,
      "text": "For more information and to find out how to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 12.46,
      "end": 16.52,
      "text": "Recorded by Marion Brown, Toronto, Canada.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 18.08,
      "end": 22.74,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables, The Hair and The Hound, number 15.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 24.06,
      "end": 28.4,
      "text": "A hound started a hair from her form and pursued her for some distance,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 29.3,
      "end": 32.48,
      "text": "but as she gradually gained upon him he gave up the chase.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 33.4,
      "end": 38.64,
      "text": "A rustic who had seen the race met the hound as he was returning and taunted him with his defeat.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 39.42,
      "end": 41.94,
      "text": "The little one was too much for you, said he.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 42.54,
      "end": 46.78,
      "text": "All well said the hound. Don't forget, it's one thing to be running for your dinner,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 47.44,
      "end": 49.6,
      "text": "but quite another to be running for your life.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 50.56,
      "end": 52.98,
      "text": "End of the hair and the hound.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
